cs.CV, cs.MM, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.GR 

This paper is about single image superresolution (SISR) which is a computer vision task related to image processing and computer graphics. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a new dataset and a new model for SISR, which involves machine learning techniques such as deep neural networks. Therefore, it is also likely to belong to cs.MM (Multimedia), cs.LG (Machine Learning), and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper involves image registration and kernel prediction, which are related to geometric and signal processing. Therefore, it is also possible to belong to cs.GR (Graphics).
